1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper focuses on privacy-preserving cluster analysis in IoMT, which involves sensitive medical data. Therefore, it is highly likely that this paper belongs to the Cryptography and Security sub-category.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a machine learning approach for processing the data involved in IoMT for medical analysis and disease diagnosis. Therefore, it is highly likely that this paper belongs to the Machine Learning sub-category.
3. cs.DB (Databases): The paper proposes an Efficient Differentially Private Data Clustering scheme (EDPDCS) based on MapReduce framework. Therefore, it is likely that this paper belongs to the Databases sub-category.
4. cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the challenges and changes brought by the emergence and rapid development of the Internet of Medical Things (IoMT) to modern medical and healthcare systems. Therefore, it is possible that this paper belongs to the Computers and Society sub-category.
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper proposes an improved initial centroids selection method to increase the accuracy and efficiency of the clustering algorithm. Therefore, it is possible that this paper belongs to the Information Retrieval sub-category.
